Kim Yong Nam Meets Iranian Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly talk with the delegation of the Physical Education Organization of Iran led by Head Mohammad Ali Abadi, who is vice-president of Iran, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Mun Jae Dok, chairman of the Korean Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, officials concerned and Hamid Reza Sadegh, Iranian charge d'affaires a.i. here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion the head of the delegation said that it is the firm stand of the Iranian government to boost relations of friendship with the DPRK. And he declared that Iran would further develop the relations of cooperation with the DPRK in different fields including sports.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Iranian Government 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a gift from the Iranian government. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was handed to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, by Iranian Vice-President Mohammad Ali Abadi on a visit to the DPRK on Thursday.

Talks between Delegations of DPRK and Iran Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- Talks between the delegation of the Korean Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission and the delegation of the Physical Education Organisation of Iran were held in Pyongyang on December 12. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the DPRK side were the members of the delegation of the DPRK Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission led by Chairman Mun Jae Dok and from the Iranian side the members of the delegation of the Physical Education Organisation of Iran led by Head Mohammad Ali Abadi, who is vice-president of Iran, and Iranian Charge d'Affaires a.i. here Hamid Reza Sadegh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on boosting the cooperative relations between the two countries in the field of sports.

DPRK, China Cooperate in Science and Technology 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- A protocol of the 42nd meeting of the DPRK-China intergovernmental committee for cooperation in science and technology was inked in Pyongyang on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the signing ceremony from the DPRK side were Ri Song Uk, vice-president of the State Academy of Sciences, and officials concerned and from the Chinese side were members of the Chinese government scientific and technological delegation led by Cheng Jinpei, vice-minister of Science and Technology, and Liu Xiaoming, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The protocol was signed by Ri Song Uk and Cheng Jinpei.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- A seminar was held at the Central Youth Hall Thursday to mark the 25th anniversary of the publication of Kim Jong Il's famous work "On Increasing Obedience to Socialist Laws".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work clarifies that it is the obedience to the socialist laws for all members of the society to work and live as required by laws and regulations instituted by the socialist state and explains the position of the socialist laws in the obedience to laws. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar heard papers proving in depth the validity and vitality of the ideas and theories expounded by Kim Jong Il in the work and explaining the issues arising in increasing the obedience to the socialist laws. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers said that the work provides ideological and theoretical guidelines for consolidating the state social system and powerfully pushing forward the revolution and construction in the DPRK as it specifies the fundamental mission of the socialist laws and duty to be fulfilled by law-enforcement officials and comprehensively indicates the orientation of increasing the obedience to the socialist laws with the revolutionary spirit and fighting trait displayed by the servicepersons of the Korean People's Army as examples and ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il in the work scientifically and theoretically formulated and systematized the idea of President Kim Il Sung on obedience to socialist laws and developed it in depth as required by the Songun era, thus helping all members of society abide by the socialist laws with high revolutionary and voluntary spirit and a high sense of organization and discipline. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers explained practical issues arising in increasing the obedience to the socialist laws so as to strictly abide by law and order of the state and give full play to the advantages of the system whereby to guide the obedience to the socialist laws. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the seminar were Vice-President Yang Hyong Sop and Secretary General Choe Yong Rim of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, members of the socialist law observance guidance committees of different levels, officials of juridical organs, law-enforcement officials and explainers of law observance, teachers and researchers of universities.

New Book Sees Light 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- The Literature and Art Publishing House published full-length novel "Stars Shine" written by Ri Tong Gu and Ri Ryong Chol from a cycle of novels "On the Road of Loyalty" created by the April 15 Writing Group recently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The novel was written with the period from late Juche 34 (1945) to early Juche 37 (1948) as its setting. It tells about how energetically anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk worked to implement the line of building regular revolutionary armed forces put forward by President Kim Il Sung right after the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through the moving stories about how the revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK were built up into invincible regular armed forces the novel artistically represents the fact that the DPRK has revolutionary armed forces today thanks to Kim Jong Suk who dedicated her whole life to the work to uphold the idea and leadership of the President like sunflower.

National Exhibition of Landscape Paintings and Handicrafts Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- A national exhibition of landscape paintings and handicrafts was held at the Pyongyang International Cultural Centre on Dec. 12 on the occasion of the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artists of fine art production institutions across the country including the Mansudae Art Studio, the National Art Studio and Pyongyang University of Fine Arts presented more than 400 pieces of landscape paintings and handicrafts of various themes to the exhibition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The works truthfully depict historic battle sites and sites associated with the history of the revolutionary activities of the three generals of Mt. Paektu and the appearance of the socialist country where the noble desire of Kim Jong Suk has come true, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the center of the exhibition hall was an oil painting showing Kim Jong Suk leaving immortal handwritings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on display were landscape paintings and handicrafts dealing with the great vitality and might of the Songun politics and the scenic beauty of the country and the long history and culture of the nation.

DPRK Shooters Prove Successful  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- Shooters of the DPRK bagged three gold medals at the 11th Asian Shooting Championships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They took the first places in the men's team event of the 25-meter standard pistol competition and the women's team event of the skeet shooting. Meanwhile, Pak Jong Ran came first in the women's individual event of the skeet shooting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 DPRK shooters also bagged silver medals in the women's team event of the trap shooting and the men's individual event of the 25-meter standard pistol. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They snatched bronze medals in the women's team event and the men's individual event of the 10-meter air pistol, in the women's individual event of the trap shooting, in the men's individual event of the 25-meter standard pistol and in the women's individual event of the skeet shooting.

Fruitful Year of Juche Literature and Art
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- Juche 96 (2007) has witnessed an efflorescence of the Juche literature and art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The stage work "Blue Sky over My Country" (Part Dawn), which consummates the Songun literature and art, depicts on a grand epical canvas the gigantic efforts of the Korean people who are on the general march of Songun revolution toward the dawn of a great, prosperous and powerful nation, thus stirring up their revolutionary fervor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The grand gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang," a world famous masterpiece, was registered in the Guinness World Records to be handed down through generations as a treasure of human culture and art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The song "The Glow over Kangson," a masterpiece of the times, was newly arranged for instrumental music and soprano trio. The song inspires all the people to live and work in the spirit of Chollima. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The performance of servicepersons of companies of the Korean People's Army who participated in the 31st art festival of KPA servicepersons and the10th joint performance of art groups of servicepersons' families of the KPA, which were appreciated as the paragon of the Songun culture, and the performance of the art group of employees in the Hungnam Fertilizer Complex show the high standard of art popularization in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Dozens of revolutionary poems and novels have seen the light this year, which has been recorded as a year in the annals for building a great, prosperous and powerful nation. Among them there are the epics "The Supreme Commander and Comrades-in-arms", "The Land of Spring in April" and "Envy the Youth of Mt. Paektu", and "Chongsan Plain" which belong to the cycle of novels "Immortal History" and novel "Ushering in the New Day" (first volume). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
