�@At the 11th Wuqiao International Acrobatics Festival, Korean acrobats performed the aerial trapeze "Diverse Flight" and were honored with "Gold Lion Prize" Cup, the highest prize, and certificate, thus demonstrating the might of the Juche acrobatics.

Pyongyang Circus
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- "Gold Lion Prize" Cup, the highest prize, was awarded to DPRK's aerial trapeze "Diverse Flight" at the 11th Wuqiao International Acrobatics Festival held in China recently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers are acrobats of the Pyongyang Circus who successfully presented latest technical movements for aerial flight such as treble flip-flap with simultaneous pirouette, quadruple flip-flap in the air and 16-meter-long distance flight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pyongyang Circus (then State Pyongyang Circus) founded on June 10, Juche 41 (1952) is one of the most famous acrobatic art groups in the country, winning fame at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first work of aerial fight was staged in May 1957. From the 1970s, it developed as one of traditional programs of the country's acrobatics, and now dominates the world in this program. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Aerial Swing Flight", "Cycle Stunt" and "Tightrope-Walking" won in the 5th International Acrobatic Festival held in France. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Aerial Somersault Flight", "Three-stage Trapeze Flight", "Flying Girls", "Fliers", "Aerial Iron Bar Flight", "Double Trapeze Flight" and others were also awarded gold prize, technical prize and special prize in international acrobatic festivals including the Monte Carlo International Acrobatic Festival, World Acrobatic Championship, World Acrobatic Olympic Festival, Wuhan International Acrobatic Festival, Rome International Acrobatic Festival and Wuqiao International Acrobatics Festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The circus has created more than 1,000 acrobatic pieces and staged tens of thousands of performances over the last years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lot of its acrobats have been conferred high state orders and honorable titles.

Koreans Called upon to Give Momentum to Atmosphere of Reconciliation and Unity
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- All Koreans are called upon to give further momentum to the atmosphere of reconciliation and unity and boost their solidarity and alliance with a view to proudly glorifying the June 15 era of reunification and bringing earlier the historic day of independent reunification. This call is made by a signed article of Rodong Sinmun Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unity is what keeps the nation alive and serves as an engine propelling the cause of reunification, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the Koreans, a homogeneous nation, the issue of unity is vital to the nation and indispensable for the national prosperity. Koreans should go united not only for their existence but for national prosperity and the demonstration of the might of the nation to the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National unity is essentially required by the nature and characteristics of the struggle for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koreans were not split because of any contradictions and conflicting elements within the nation. The issue of Korea's reunification is not aimed to eliminate any contradictions within the nation or remove institutional antagonism but to rejoin the blood ties of the nation severed by the foreign forces and achieve national reconciliation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is unbearable national misfortune and tragedy for the Koreans to have been forced to live separated in the north and south for over six decades due to the outside forces. All Koreans should go united in order to put an end to this tragedy of the national history at an early date. The reconciliation and unity of the entire nation precisely mean the reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Outsiders and ultra-right conservatives of south Korea, their lackeys, have spoken ill of "By our nation itself," the idea common to the nation, by hook or by crook, displeased with it. Lurking behind this is their sinister intention to deter the Koreans from achieving the national unity and foster antipathy and confrontation among fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans should work harder to achieve the unity of the entire nation on the basis of the achievements made in the course of the struggle for unity.

Kim Il Sung's Work Published in Nicaragua
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 13 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung's famous work "For a Free and Peaceful New World" was published in pamphlet by a Nicaraguan publishing house on Dec. 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on April 29, Juche 80(1991), clarifies the tasks for building a free and peaceful new world and ways to do so.

Search for Tokushima Prefectural Headquarters of Chongryon Protested
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, December 11 (KNS-KCNA) -- Officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) in Jushikoku Area of Japan went to the Tokushima prefectural police station on Dec. 4 and lodged a protest with the prefectural police authorities against their frantic fascist search operation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In a written protest they condemned the prefectural police authorities for searching the prefectural headquarters after faking up what they called "fraud and swindle" as regards social insurance and confiscating a lot of articles which had nothing to do with it on Nov. 28. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They termed this an unpardonable politically motivated suppression of Chongryon, adding that it was quite an unreasonable action for the police to have searched even the prefectural headquarters of Chongryon because if there would be anything wrong with the application for social insurance it was the issue to be settled by the social insurance office. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They strongly demanded the police authorities apologize for the search operation against the prefectural headquarters, stop at once the unreasonable investigation and immediately return the confiscated articles.

Iniciadas conversaciones militares a nivel de general N-S
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 13 de diciembre (ATCC) -- Quedaron iniciadas la vispera en la parte Sur de Phanmunjom la 7a ronda de las conversaciones militares a nivel de general entre el Norte y el Sur de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A esa cita participaron la delegacion de la parte Norte encabezada por el teniente general del Ejercito Popular de Corea, Kim Yong Chol, y la de la parte Sur presidida por el delegado-jefe Ri Hong Gi, jefe de Planificacion de Politica del Ministerio de Defensa Nacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ambas partes discutieron las medidas para garantizar en lo militar la cooperacion y el intercambio bilaterales en la "Zona especial de cooperacion pacifica del Mar Oeste" segun el acuerdo logrado en la segunda ronda de las conversaciones entre los ministros de las fuerzas armadas Norte-Sur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Sobre todo, el jefe de la delegacion nortena ratifico la invariable posicion del EPC de asegurar consecuentemente en sentido militar la ejecucion de la historica Declaracion del 4 de Octubre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Expreso la posicion de tomar medidas con rumbo a aumentar el tiempo del paso en la Zona Industrial de Kaesong y la Zona Turistica del monte Kumgang, asegurar la rapidez y flexibilidad de las comunicaciones y a acortar el tiempo de la tramitacion aduanera en estas zonas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Lamento que en cuanto al problema del Mar Oeste, la parte Sur pone escollos artificiales en la solucion de este asunto sin cambiar su posicion de siempre en contraposicion a la imparcial y justa propuesta y sinceros esfuerzos de la parte Norte. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A continuacion, presento el borrador del acuerdo sobre la fijacion del area de pesca conjunta y la franja de paz en el Mar Oeste, que refleja la imparcial y justa posicion de la parte Norte. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ese documento aborda el problema de determinar dichas zonas en el principio de fomentar los intereses y prosperidad comunes de la nacion y preservar la paz, las medidas para garantizar en lo militar la cooperacion en ellas, los remedios para mantener apartadas a sus respectivas fuerzas navales enfrentadas en el Mar Oeste, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por ultimo, expreso su esperanza de que la parte Sur de una respuesta positiva a la propuesta de la parte Norte tras examinarla seriamente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le siguio en usar la palabra el delegado-jefe de la parte Sur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Las conversaciones continuan.

Kim Jong Il recibe presente del gobierno irani
